---
title: Cheesy French Onion Chicken with Garlic Bread & Lemony Roasted Carrots
description: We can never resist a rich, brothy bowl of French onion soup—especially when it’s topped with a crouton and cloaked in a layer of melty cheese. That’s why we were over the moon when our chefs brought all those same flavors and textures to this weeknight dinner. Seared chicken cutlets are topped with caramelized onion that’s cooked down with beef stock, fresh thyme, and butter. Next, they’re smothered in gooey Swiss cheese. Of course, we couldn’t forget the crusty dipper—here, it’s homemade garlic bread for soaking up every last drop of sauce. Now, what should we French onion next?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/615db59fbeeacb7f92644b09-30ef789f.jpg
